  "description": "A balanced South Indian lunch bowl where legumes, vegetables, and whole grains carry the dish instead of excess fat. Pudalangai Paal Kootu with Red Rice brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Cook the vegetable with 250 ml water and salt over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes until just tender.",
    "Add the cooked legume and the coconut paste and simmer on low heat for 5 minutes, stirring often so the base does not catch.",
    "In a small pan, heat oil on medium heat, crackle mustard and urad dal, then add curry leaves. Pour this tempering over the kootu immediately.",
    "Fold once, rest 2 minutes for the flavors to settle, and serve with the cooked grain."
  ],
